name: Candy from strangers - Orange and blue
description:
@Sugartivi | Dear art collector, how do you know whom to trust? In my 90’s childhood, stranger danger was literally educated into me. But the most damaging people are often under the radar, or aren’t actually strangers. 

This piece explores things that look sweet but might not be, including items such as durian candy, that were involved in food poisoning incidents. The composition itself evokes airport scanners and children’s “i spy” books, aiming for a sense of free-floating unease.
